==Prevention==
{{Main|Suicide prevention}}
[[File:Suicide prevention-DOD.jpg|thumb|350px|<center>'''Suicide prevention poster'''</center><br><table border="1" align="right" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="350px"  bgcolor="#E2DEDE" colspan="3">
<tr>
<th><center><big>'''Warning Signs of Suicide'''</big></center></th></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#F2EDED">

* Talking about wanting to die; <br>
* Looking for a way to kill oneself; <br>
* Talking about feeling hopeless or having no purpose; <br>
* Talking about feeling trapped or being in unbearable pain; <br>
* Talking about being a burden to others; <br>
* Increasing the use of alcohol or drugs; <br>
* Acting anxious, agitated, or reckless; <br>
* Sleeping too little or too much; <br>
* Withdrawing or feeling isolated; <br>
* Showing rage or talking about seeking revenge; <br>
* Displaying extreme mood swings. <br>

The more of these signs a person shows, the greater the risk of suicide. Warning signs are associated with suicide but may not be what causes a suicide.<br><br>
'''What To Do'''
<br>
Do not leave the person alone;  Remove any objects that could be used in a suicide attempt;  Call a [[List of suicide crisis lines|suicide prevention crisis line]]; and  Take the person to an emergency room or seek help from a medical or mental health professional.
